# Optimize Bento Grid Performance and Fix Border Alignment

The site is currently slow due to unconstrained SVG filters causing massive redraws. Additionally, the border light is misaligned because it's being "squeezed" by parent padding. I will refactor the container structure and optimize the animation.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I am moving the internal padding (`p-4`) of the Bento items to a nested content wrapper. This ensures the `BorderBeam` can fill the ENTIRE border-box without being constrained by the content padding.

## Proposed Changes

### Component: [BentoGrid.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/components/BentoGrid.tsx)

#### [MODIFY] [BentoGridItem](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/components/BentoGrid.tsx)
- Move the `p-4` (padding) class from the outer container to a new inner content `div`.
- This allows `BorderBeam` (which is `absolute inset-0`) to truly occupy the full space bounded by the border.
- Ensure the outer container remains the positioning context (`relative`) and handles the `overflow-hidden`.

### Component: [BorderBeam.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/components/ui/border-beam.tsx)

#### [MODIFY] [BorderBeam.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/prod-2-adecos/src/components/ui/border-beam.tsx)
- **Optimize Filters:** 
    - Remove the heavy SVG `<filter>` and `feGaussianBlur`.
    - Use CSS `filter: blur()` instead, which is hardware-accelerated and more efficient.
- **Contain Repaints:**
    - Set `overflow: hidden` on the SVG to prevent the glow from bleeding across the entire screen.
    - Reduce the filter region size to prevent the browser from calculating blurs for out-of-bounds areas.
- **Alignment Fix:**
    - Explicitly set `top: 0`, `left: 0`, `width: 100%`, `height: 100%` on the SVG to ensure it fills the parent border box.
    - Synchronize the `rx` value with the parent's actual corner radius.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Manual Verification
- **Performance:** Monitor FPS during scroll and hover in the browser. Verify that the "blue bars" at the top/bottom of the screen are gone.
- **Alignment:** Verify the beam covers the full height of the tall left box and matches all corners exactly.
- **Light/Dark Mode:** Ensure the hover effect remains visible and elegant in both themes.
